6	//! Async Vector Addition Example
7	//!
8	//! Demonstrates the cuda-async execution model:
9	//! - `#[cuda_module]` generates typed async launch methods
10	//! - `vecadd_async` returns a lazy `DeviceOperation`, no GPU work yet
11	//! - `.await` schedules it on a round-robin stream pool and waits
12	//! - `.sync()` does the same but blocks the calling thread
13	//! - `and_then` chains operations on the same stream
14	//! - `zip!` runs independent operations on the same stream
15	//!
16	//! Build and run with:
17	//!   cargo oxide run async_vecadd
